
   Calculates minimal distance between atoms read from a cif file.


   -M, --distance-matrix           set distance matrix output format.
   -P, --pairewise-distance        set pairwise distance output format.
   -O, --original-atoms            print atoms read from cif file.
   -S, --symetrical-atoms          print atoms generated by applying
                                   symmetry operators.
   -H, --shifted-atoms             print atoms generated by shifting
                                   all the atoms of the first octant.
   -d, --precision                 number of fraction digits displayed  
                                   in distance matrix distances.
   -l, --matrix-line-length        maximum length of an output line in
                                   distance matrix.
   -F, --print-filename            add a filename field to the end of 
                                   pairwise distance format lines.
   --no-original-atoms             do not print original atoms.
   --no-symetrical-atoms           do not print symetrical atoms.
   --no-shifted-atoms              do not print shifted atoms.
   --no-filename                   do not print filename in distance 
                                   matrix format
   --help,--usage                  prints this message and quits.

